<dl id="n12229b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12229b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12229b"> 229(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> whitebearded</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">One afternoon, his legs dangling over the edge of the stone quarry, he fell asleep, and in his dream the Big Man &mdash; a <mark>white-bearded</mark>, vigorous, stern, elderly giant, broad as the front of Capel Sion and taller than the roof &mdash; came to him, saying: &ldquo;Eben bach, why for now do you waste your days in sleep Go you, little son, and dig a hole in the place where stood Old Shaci&apos;s hut.&rdquo; <small> Caradoc Evans, <a name="EVAN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EVAN"><cite title="source">My People</cite></a> (1915) 68-69 [The Talent Thou Gavest]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
